_raw.rds` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mk_raw.rds under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gV0J5SpX1xwebU5G6C6koHWJ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use the methRead function from methylKit to read the bismark coverage files located in the input directory. Set the pipeline parameter to 'bismarkCoverage', mincov to 4, treatment to c(0, 0, 0), and assembly to 'mock_v1'.\\n3. Save the resulting methylRawList object to 'output/mk_raw.rds' using saveRDS.\\n4. Verify that the file 'output/mk_raw.rds' has been created.\\n5. If the file exists, call submit_done(success=true) to complete the task.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_load`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_load\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `early`, difficulty: `1`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n